# Loyalty Rewards App

A simple, cloud-based loyalty rewards system for small businesses. Customers check in with their phone number, and businesses can easily track visits and reward loyalty.

---

## Features

- Fast, contactless customer check-in
- Real-time rewards tracking
- Easy-to-use interface for staff and customers
- Works on any device
- Secure and scalable (React frontend, Node.js/MongoDB backend)

---

## How It Works

1. Customer enters their phone number at checkout.
2. The system logs the visit and tracks rewards.
3. Customers receive rewards after a set number of visits.

---

## Technology Stack

- **Frontend:** React (see [`client`](./client))
- **Backend:** Node.js, Express, MongoDB (see [`server`](./server))
- **Database:** MongoDB (local by default, can use MongoDB Atlas)

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js & npm
- MongoDB (local or Atlas)

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/x88-code/loyalty-rewards-app.git
   cd loyalty-rewards-app-mongo
   ```

2. **Backend Setup:**
   ```sh
   cd server
   npm install
   # By default, connects to mongodb://localhost:27017/loyalty_rewards
   # To use MongoDB Atlas, set the MONGO_URI environment variable
   npm run dev
   ```

3. **Frontend Setup:**
   ```sh
   cd ../client
   npm install
   npm start
   ```

4. **Access the app:**
   - Frontend: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)
   - Backend/API: [http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000)

---

## Environment Variables

- **Backend:**  
  - `MONGO_URI` — (optional) Your MongoDB connection string. Defaults to local MongoDB.
- **Frontend:**  
  - `REACT_APP_API_URL` — (optional) URL of your backend API (defaults to `http://localhost:5000`)

---

## Usage

- Customers check in by entering their phone number.
- Each check-in increments their visit count.
- Progress bar shows visits toward next reward.

---

## Deployment

- **Frontend:** Deploy to [Vercel](https://vercel.com) or similar
- **Backend:** Deploy to [Render](https://render.com) or similar

